-- EU `Firmly' Denies Report That It, IMF, U.S. Preparing Spain Credit Line
-- Kevin Costelloe
-- 2010-06-16T06:32:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/eu-firmly-denies-report-that-it-imf-u-s-preparing-spain-credit-line.html

          
          
             The European Union today ‘firmly’
denied a report that the International Monetary Fund, the EU the
U.S. Treasury are putting together a credit line of as much as
250 billion euros for the Spanish government. “I can firmly
deny it,” European Commission spokesman Amadeu Altafaj said
this morning in response to the report in El Economista. He said
no such plan is being prepared for Spain.  
          
          


  


        